3597/**
3598 * ftrace_regex_open - initialize function tracer filter files
3599 * @ops: The ftrace_ops that hold the hash filters
3600 * @flag: The type of filter to process
3601 * @inode: The inode, usually passed in to your open routine
3602 * @file: The file, usually passed in to your open routine
3603 *
3604 * ftrace_regex_open() initializes the filter files for the
3605 * @ops. Depending on @flag it may process the filter hash or
3606 * the notrace hash of @ops. With this called from the open
3607 * routine, you can use ftrace_filter_write() for the write
3608 * routine if @flag has FTRACE_ITER_FILTER set, or
3609 * ftrace_notrace_write() if @flag has FTRACE_ITER_NOTRACE set.
3610 * tracing_lseek() should be used as the lseek routine, and
3611 * release must call ftrace_regex_release().
3612 */
3613int
3614ftrace_regex_open(struct ftrace_ops *ops, int flag,
3615 struct inode *inode, struct file *file)
3616{
3617 struct ftrace_iterator *iter;
3618 struct ftrace_hash *hash;
3619 struct list_head *mod_head;
3620 struct trace_array *tr = ops->private;
3621 int ret = 0;
3622
3623 ftrace_ops_init(ops);
3624
3625 if (unlikely(ftrace_disabled))
3626 return -ENODEV;
3627
3628 iter = kzalloc(sizeof(*iter), GFP_KERNEL);
3629 if (!iter)
3630 return -ENOMEM;
3631
3632 if (trace_parser_get_init(&iter->parser, FTRACE_BUFF_MAX)) {
3633 kfree(iter);
3634 return -ENOMEM;
3635 }
3636
3637 iter->ops = ops;
3638 iter->flags = flag;
3639 iter->tr = tr;
3640
3641 mutex_lock(&ops->func_hash->regex_lock);
3642
3643 if (flag & FTRACE_ITER_NOTRACE) {
3644 hash = ops->func_hash->notrace_hash;
3645 mod_head = tr ? &tr->mod_notrace : NULL;
3646 } else {
3647 hash = ops->func_hash->filter_hash;
3648 mod_head = tr ? &tr->mod_trace : NULL;
3649 }
3650
3651 iter->mod_list = mod_head;
3652
3653 if (file->f_mode & FMODE_WRITE) {
3654 const int size_bits = FTRACE_HASH_DEFAULT_BITS;
3655
3656 if (file->f_flags & O_TRUNC) {
3657 iter->hash = alloc_ftrace_hash(size_bits);
3658 clear_ftrace_mod_list(mod_head);
3659 } else {
3660 iter->hash = alloc_and_copy_ftrace_hash(size_bits, hash);
3661 }
3662
3663 if (!iter->hash) {
3664 trace_parser_put(&iter->parser);
3665 kfree(iter);
3666 ret = -ENOMEM;
3667 goto out_unlock;
3668 }
3669 } else
3670 iter->hash = hash;
3671
3672 if (file->f_mode & FMODE_READ) {
3673 iter->pg = ftrace_pages_start;
3674
3675 ret = seq_open(file, &show_ftrace_seq_ops);
3676 if (!ret) {
3677 struct seq_file *m = file->private_data;
3678 m->private = iter;
3679 } else {
3680 /* Failed */
3681 free_ftrace_hash(iter->hash);
3682 trace_parser_put(&iter->parser);
3683 kfree(iter);
3684 }
3685 } else
3686 file->private_data = iter;
3687
3688 out_unlock:
3689 mutex_unlock(&ops->func_hash->regex_lock);
3690
3691 return ret;
3692}

3700 FTRACE_ITER_FILTER | FTRACE_ITER_DO_PROBES,
3701 inode, file);

3720/*
3721 * If symbols in an architecture don't correspond exactly to the user-visible
3722 * name of what they represent, it is possible to define this function to
3723 * perform the necessary adjustments.
3724*/
3725char * __weak arch_ftrace_match_adjust(char *str, const char *search)
3726{
3727 return str;
3728}
3729
3730static int ftrace_match(char *str, struct ftrace_glob *g)
3731{
3732 int matched = 0;
3733 int slen;
3734
3735 str = arch_ftrace_match_adjust(str, g->search);
3736
3737 switch (g->type) {
3738 case MATCH_FULL:
3739 if (strcmp(str, g->search) == 0)
3740 matched = 1;
3741 break;
3742 case MATCH_FRONT_ONLY:
3743 if (strncmp(str, g->search, g->len) == 0)
3744 matched = 1;
3745 break;
3746 case MATCH_MIDDLE_ONLY:
3747 if (strstr(str, g->search))
3748 matched = 1;
3749 break;
3750 case MATCH_END_ONLY:
3751 slen = strlen(str);
3752 if (slen >= g->len &&
3753 memcmp(str + slen - g->len, g->search, g->len) == 0)
3754 matched = 1;
3755 break;
3756 case MATCH_GLOB:
3757 if (glob_match(g->search, str))
3758 matched = 1;
3759 break;
3760 }
3761
3762 return matched;
3763}
3764
3765static int
3766enter_record(struct ftrace_hash *hash, struct dyn_ftrace *rec, int clear_filter)
3767{
3768 struct ftrace_func_entry *entry;
3769 int ret = 0;
3770
3771 entry = ftrace_lookup_ip(hash, rec->ip);
3772 if (clear_filter) {
3773 /* Do nothing if it doesn't exist */
3774 if (!entry)
3775 return 0;
3776
3777 free_hash_entry(hash, entry);
3778 } else {
3779 /* Do nothing if it exists */
3780 if (entry)
3781 return 0;
3782
3783 ret = add_hash_entry(hash, rec->ip);
3784 }
3785 return ret;
3786}
3787
3788static int
3789ftrace_match_record(struct dyn_ftrace *rec, struct ftrace_glob *func_g,
3790 struct ftrace_glob *mod_g, int exclude_mod)
3791{
3792 char str[KSYM_SYMBOL_LEN];
3793 char *modname;
3794
3795 kallsyms_lookup(rec->ip, NULL, NULL, &modname, str);
3796
3797 if (mod_g) {
3798 int mod_matches = (modname) ? ftrace_match(modname, mod_g) : 0;
3799
3800 /* blank module name to match all modules */
3801 if (!mod_g->len) {
3802 /* blank module globbing: modname xor exclude_mod */
3803 if (!exclude_mod != !modname)
3804 goto func_match;
3805 return 0;
3806 }
3807
3808 /*
3809 * exclude_mod is set to trace everything but the given
3810 * module. If it is set and the module matches, then
3811 * return 0. If it is not set, and the module doesn't match
3812 * also return 0. Otherwise, check the function to see if
3813 * that matches.
3814 */
3815 if (!mod_matches == !exclude_mod)
3816 return 0;
3817func_match:
3818 /* blank search means to match all funcs in the mod */
3819 if (!func_g->len)
3820 return 1;
3821 }
3822
3823 return ftrace_match(str, func_g);
3824}
3825
3826static int
3827match_records(struct ftrace_hash *hash, char *func, int len, char *mod)
3828{
3829 struct ftrace_page *pg;
3830 struct dyn_ftrace *rec;
3831 struct ftrace_glob func_g = { .type = MATCH_FULL };
3832 struct ftrace_glob mod_g = { .type = MATCH_FULL };
3833 struct ftrace_glob *mod_match = (mod) ? &mod_g : NULL;
3834 int exclude_mod = 0;
3835 int found = 0;
3836 int ret;
3837 int clear_filter = 0;
3838
3839 if (func) {
3840 func_g.type = filter_parse_regex(func, len, &func_g.search,
3841 &clear_filter);
3842 func_g.len = strlen(func_g.search);
3843 }
3844
3845 if (mod) {
3846 mod_g.type = filter_parse_regex(mod, strlen(mod),
3847 &mod_g.search, &exclude_mod);
3848 mod_g.len = strlen(mod_g.search);
3849 }
3850
3851 mutex_lock(&ftrace_lock);
3852
3853 if (unlikely(ftrace_disabled))
3854 goto out_unlock;
3855
3856 do_for_each_ftrace_rec(pg, rec) {
3857
3858 if (rec->flags & FTRACE_FL_DISABLED)
3859 continue;
3860
3861 if (ftrace_match_record(rec, &func_g, mod_match, exclude_mod)) {
3862 ret = enter_record(hash, rec, clear_filter);
3863 if (ret < 0) {
3864 found = ret;
3865 goto out_unlock;
3866 }
3867 found = 1;
3868 }
3869 } while_for_each_ftrace_rec();
3870 out_unlock:
3871 mutex_unlock(&ftrace_lock);
3872
3873 return found;
3874}
3875
3876static int
3877ftrace_match_records(struct ftrace_hash *hash, char *buff, int len)
3878{
3879 return match_records(hash, buff, len, NULL);
3880}
3881
3882static void ftrace_ops_update_code(struct ftrace_ops *ops,
3883 struct ftrace_ops_hash *old_hash)
3884{
3885 struct ftrace_ops *op;
3886
3887 if (!ftrace_enabled)
3888 return;
3889
3890 if (ops->flags & FTRACE_OPS_FL_ENABLED) {
3891 ftrace_run_modify_code(ops, FTRACE_UPDATE_CALLS, old_hash);
3892 return;
3893 }
3894
3895 /*
3896 * If this is the shared global_ops filter, then we need to
3897 * check if there is another ops that shares it, is enabled.
3898 * If so, we still need to run the modify code.
3899 */
3900 if (ops->func_hash != &global_ops.local_hash)
3901 return;
3902
3903 do_for_each_ftrace_op(op, ftrace_ops_list) {
3904 if (op->func_hash == &global_ops.local_hash &&
3905 op->flags & FTRACE_OPS_FL_ENABLED) {
3906 ftrace_run_modify_code(op, FTRACE_UPDATE_CALLS, old_hash);
3907 /* Only need to do this once */
3908 return;
3909 }
3910 } while_for_each_ftrace_op(op);
3911}
3912
3913static int ftrace_hash_move_and_update_ops(struct ftrace_ops *ops,
3914 struct ftrace_hash **orig_hash,
3915 struct ftrace_hash *hash,
3916 int enable)
3917{
3918 struct ftrace_ops_hash old_hash_ops;
3919 struct ftrace_hash *old_hash;
3920 int ret;
3921
3922 old_hash = *orig_hash;
3923 old_hash_ops.filter_hash = ops->func_hash->filter_hash;
3924 old_hash_ops.notrace_hash = ops->func_hash->notrace_hash;
3925 ret = ftrace_hash_move(ops, enable, orig_hash, hash);
3926 if (!ret) {
3927 ftrace_ops_update_code(ops, &old_hash_ops);
3928 free_ftrace_hash_rcu(old_hash);
3929 }
3930 return ret;
3931}
3932
3933static bool module_exists(const char *module)
3934{
3935 /* All modules have the symbol __this_module */
3936 const char this_mod[] = "__this_module";
3937 const int modname_size = MAX_PARAM_PREFIX_LEN + sizeof(this_mod) + 1;
3938 char modname[modname_size + 1];
3939 unsigned long val;
3940 int n;
3941
3942 n = snprintf(modname, modname_size + 1, "%s:%s", module, this_mod);
3943
3944 if (n > modname_size)
3945 return false;
3946
3947 val = module_kallsyms_lookup_name(modname);
3948 return val != 0;
3949}
3950
3951static int cache_mod(struct trace_array *tr,
3952 const char *func, char *module, int enable)
3953{
3954 struct ftrace_mod_load *ftrace_mod, *n;
3955 struct list_head *head = enable ? &tr->mod_trace : &tr->mod_notrace;
3956 int ret;
3957
3958 mutex_lock(&ftrace_lock);
3959
3960 /* We do not cache inverse filters */
3961 if (func[0] == '!') {
3962 func++;
3963 ret = -EINVAL;
3964
3965 /* Look to remove this hash */
3966 list_for_each_entry_safe(ftrace_mod, n, head, list) {
3967 if (strcmp(ftrace_mod->module, module) != 0)
3968 continue;
3969
3970 /* no func matches all */
3971 if (strcmp(func, "*") == 0 ||
3972 (ftrace_mod->func &&
3973 strcmp(ftrace_mod->func, func) == 0)) {
3974 ret = 0;
3975 free_ftrace_mod(ftrace_mod);
3976 continue;
3977 }
3978 }
3979 goto out;
3980 }
3981
3982 ret = -EINVAL;
3983 /* We only care about modules that have not been loaded yet */
3984 if (module_exists(module))
3985 goto out;
3986
3987 /* Save this string off, and execute it when the module is loaded */
3988 ret = ftrace_add_mod(tr, func, module, enable);
3989 out:
3990 mutex_unlock(&ftrace_lock);
3991
3992 return ret;
3993}

4000static void process_mod_list(struct list_head *head, struct ftrace_ops *ops,
4001 char *mod, bool enable)
4002{
4003 struct ftrace_mod_load *ftrace_mod, *n;
4004 struct ftrace_hash **orig_hash, *new_hash;
4005 LIST_HEAD(process_mods);
4006 char *func;
4007 int ret;
4008
4009 mutex_lock(&ops->func_hash->regex_lock);
4010
4011 if (enable)
4012 orig_hash = &ops->func_hash->filter_hash;
4013 else
4014 orig_hash = &ops->func_hash->notrace_hash;
4015
4016 new_hash = alloc_and_copy_ftrace_hash(FTRACE_HASH_DEFAULT_BITS,
4017 *orig_hash);
4018 if (!new_hash)
4019 goto out; /* warn? */
4020
4021 mutex_lock(&ftrace_lock);
4022
4023 list_for_each_entry_safe(ftrace_mod, n, head, list) {
4024
4025 if (strcmp(ftrace_mod->module, mod) != 0)
4026 continue;
4027
4028 if (ftrace_mod->func)
4029 func = kstrdup(ftrace_mod->func, GFP_KERNEL);
4030 else
4031 func = kstrdup("*", GFP_KERNEL);
4032
4033 if (!func) /* warn? */
4034 continue;
4035
4036 list_del(&ftrace_mod->list);
4037 list_add(&ftrace_mod->list, &process_mods);
4038
4039 /* Use the newly allocated func, as it may be "*" */
4040 kfree(ftrace_mod->func);
4041 ftrace_mod->func = func;
4042 }
4043
4044 mutex_unlock(&ftrace_lock);
4045
4046 list_for_each_entry_safe(ftrace_mod, n, &process_mods, list) {
4047
4048 func = ftrace_mod->func;
4049
4050 /* Grabs ftrace_lock, which is why we have this extra step */
4051 match_records(new_hash, func, strlen(func), mod);
4052 free_ftrace_mod(ftrace_mod);
4053 }
4054
4055 if (enable && list_empty(head))
4056 new_hash->flags &= ~FTRACE_HASH_FL_MOD;
4057
4058 mutex_lock(&ftrace_lock);
4059
4060 ret = ftrace_hash_move_and_update_ops(ops, orig_hash,
4061 new_hash, enable);
4062 mutex_unlock(&ftrace_lock);
4063
4064 out:
4065 mutex_unlock(&ops->func_hash->regex_lock);
4066
4067 free_ftrace_hash(new_hash);
4068}

4070static void process_cached_mods(const char *mod_name)
4071{
4072 struct trace_array *tr;
4073 char *mod;
4074
4075 mod = kstrdup(mod_name, GFP_KERNEL);
4076 if (!mod)
4077 return;
4078
4079 mutex_lock(&trace_types_lock);
4080 list_for_each_entry(tr, &ftrace_trace_arrays, list) {
4081 if (!list_empty(&tr->mod_trace))
4082 process_mod_list(&tr->mod_trace, tr->ops, mod, true);
4083 if (!list_empty(&tr->mod_notrace))
4084 process_mod_list(&tr->mod_notrace, tr->ops, mod, false);
4085 }
4086 mutex_unlock(&trace_types_lock);
4087
4088 kfree(mod);
4089}

4092/*
4093 * We register the module command as a template to show others how
4094 * to register the a command as well.
4095 */
4096
4097static int
4098ftrace_mod_callback(struct trace_array *tr, struct ftrace_hash *hash,
4099 char *func_orig, char *cmd, char *module, int enable)
4100{
4101 char *func;
4102 int ret;
4103
4104 /* match_records() modifies func, and we need the original */
4105 func = kstrdup(func_orig, GFP_KERNEL);
4106 if (!func)
4107 return -ENOMEM;
4108
4109 /*
4110 * cmd == 'mod' because we only registered this func
4111 * for the 'mod' ftrace_func_command.
4112 * But if you register one func with multiple commands,
4113 * you can tell which command was used by the cmd
4114 * parameter.
4115 */
4116 ret = match_records(hash, func, strlen(func), module);
4117 kfree(func);
4118
4119 if (!ret)
4120 return cache_mod(tr, func_orig, module, enable);
4121 if (ret < 0)
4122 return ret;
4123 return 0;
4124}

4137static void function_trace_probe_call(unsigned long ip, unsigned long parent_ip,
4138 struct ftrace_ops *op, struct pt_regs *pt_regs)
4139{
4140 struct ftrace_probe_ops *probe_ops;
4141 struct ftrace_func_probe *probe;
4142
4143 probe = container_of(op, struct ftrace_func_probe, ops);
4144 probe_ops = probe->probe_ops;
4145
4146 /*
4147 * Disable preemption for these calls to prevent a RCU grace
4148 * period. This syncs the hash iteration and freeing of items
4149 * on the hash. rcu_read_lock is too dangerous here.
4150 */
4151 preempt_disable_notrace();
4152 probe_ops->func(ip, parent_ip, probe->tr, probe_ops, probe->data);
4153 preempt_enable_notrace();
4154}

4156struct ftrace_func_map {
4157 struct ftrace_func_entry entry;
4158 void *data;
4159};
4160
4161struct ftrace_func_mapper {
4162 struct ftrace_hash hash;
4163};
4164
4165/**
4166 * allocate_ftrace_func_mapper - allocate a new ftrace_func_mapper
4167 *
4168 * Returns a ftrace_func_mapper descriptor that can be used to map ips to data.
4169 */
4170struct ftrace_func_mapper *allocate_ftrace_func_mapper(void)
4171{
4172 struct ftrace_hash *hash;
4173
4174 /*
4175 * The mapper is simply a ftrace_hash, but since the entries
4176 * in the hash are not ftrace_func_entry type, we define it
4177 * as a separate structure.
4178 */
4179 hash = alloc_ftrace_hash(FTRACE_HASH_DEFAULT_BITS);
4180 return (struct ftrace_func_mapper *)hash;
4181}
4182
4183/**
4184 * ftrace_func_mapper_find_ip - Find some data mapped to an ip
4185 * @mapper: The mapper that has the ip maps
4186 * @ip: the instruction pointer to find the data for
4187 *
4188 * Returns the data mapped to @ip if found otherwise NULL. The return
4189 * is actually the address of the mapper data pointer. The address is
4190 * returned for use cases where the data is no bigger than a long, and
4191 * the user can use the data pointer as its data instead of having to
4192 * allocate more memory for the reference.
4193 */
4194void **ftrace_func_mapper_find_ip(struct ftrace_func_mapper *mapper,
4195 unsigned long ip)
4196{
4197 struct ftrace_func_entry *entry;
4198 struct ftrace_func_map *map;
4199
4200 entry = ftrace_lookup_ip(&mapper->hash, ip);
4201 if (!entry)
4202 return NULL;
4203
4204 map = (struct ftrace_func_map *)entry;
4205 return &map->data;
4206}
4207
4208/**
4209 * ftrace_func_mapper_add_ip - Map some data to an ip
4210 * @mapper: The mapper that has the ip maps
4211 * @ip: The instruction pointer address to map @data to
4212 * @data: The data to map to @ip
4213 *
4214 * Returns 0 on succes otherwise an error.
4215 */
4216int ftrace_func_mapper_add_ip(struct ftrace_func_mapper *mapper,
4217 unsigned long ip, void *data)
4218{
4219 struct ftrace_func_entry *entry;
4220 struct ftrace_func_map *map;
4221
4222 entry = ftrace_lookup_ip(&mapper->hash, ip);
4223 if (entry)
4224 return -EBUSY;
4225
4226 map = kmalloc(sizeof(*map), GFP_KERNEL);
4227 if (!map)
4228 return -ENOMEM;
4229
4230 map->entry.ip = ip;
4231 map->data = data;
4232
4233 __add_hash_entry(&mapper->hash, &map->entry);
4234
4235 return 0;
4236}
4237
4238/**
4239 * ftrace_func_mapper_remove_ip - Remove an ip from the mapping
4240 * @mapper: The mapper that has the ip maps
4241 * @ip: The instruction pointer address to remove the data from
4242 *
4243 * Returns the data if it is found, otherwise NULL.
4244 * Note, if the data pointer is used as the data itself, (see
4245 * ftrace_func_mapper_find_ip(), then the return value may be meaningless,
4246 * if the data pointer was set to zero.
4247 */
4248void *ftrace_func_mapper_remove_ip(struct ftrace_func_mapper *mapper,
4249 unsigned long ip)
4250{
4251 struct ftrace_func_entry *entry;
4252 struct ftrace_func_map *map;
4253 void *data;
4254
4255 entry = ftrace_lookup_ip(&mapper->hash, ip);
4256 if (!entry)
4257 return NULL;
4258
4259 map = (struct ftrace_func_map *)entry;
4260 data = map->data;
4261
4262 remove_hash_entry(&mapper->hash, entry);
4263 kfree(entry);
4264
4265 return data;
4266}
4267
4268/**
4269 * free_ftrace_func_mapper - free a mapping of ips and data
4270 * @mapper: The mapper that has the ip maps
4271 * @free_func: A function to be called on each data item.
4272 *
4273 * This is used to free the function mapper. The @free_func is optional
4274 * and can be used if the data needs to be freed as well.
4275 */
4276void free_ftrace_func_mapper(struct ftrace_func_mapper *mapper,
4277 ftrace_mapper_func free_func)
4278{
4279 struct ftrace_func_entry *entry;
4280 struct ftrace_func_map *map;
4281 struct hlist_head *hhd;
4282 int size = 1 << mapper->hash.size_bits;
4283 int i;
4284
4285 if (free_func && mapper->hash.count) {
4286 for (i = 0; i < size; i++) {
4287 hhd = &mapper->hash.buckets[i];
4288 hlist_for_each_entry(entry, hhd, hlist) {
4289 map = (struct ftrace_func_map *)entry;
4290 free_func(map);
4291 }
4292 }
4293 }
4294 free_ftrace_hash(&mapper->hash);
4295}
4296
4297static void release_probe(struct ftrace_func_probe *probe)
4298{
4299 struct ftrace_probe_ops *probe_ops;
4300
4301 mutex_lock(&ftrace_lock);
4302
4303 WARN_ON(probe->ref <= 0);
4304
4305 /* Subtract the ref that was used to protect this instance */
4306 probe->ref--;
4307
4308 if (!probe->ref) {
4309 probe_ops = probe->probe_ops;
4310 /*
4311 * Sending zero as ip tells probe_ops to free
4312 * the probe->data itself
4313 */
4314 if (probe_ops->free)
4315 probe_ops->free(probe_ops, probe->tr, 0, probe->data);
4316 list_del(&probe->list);
4317 kfree(probe);
4318 }
4319 mutex_unlock(&ftrace_lock);
4320}
4321
4322static void acquire_probe_locked(struct ftrace_func_probe *probe)
4323{
4324 /*
4325 * Add one ref to keep it from being freed when releasing the
4326 * ftrace_lock mutex.
4327 */
4328 probe->ref++;
4329}
4330
4331int
4332register_ftrace_function_probe(char *glob, struct trace_array *tr,
4333 struct ftrace_probe_ops *probe_ops,
4334 void *data)
4335{
4336 struct ftrace_func_entry *entry;
4337 struct ftrace_func_probe *probe;
4338 struct ftrace_hash **orig_hash;
4339 struct ftrace_hash *old_hash;
4340 struct ftrace_hash *hash;
4341 int count = 0;
4342 int size;
4343 int ret;
4344 int i;
4345
4346 if (WARN_ON(!tr))
4347 return -EINVAL;
4348
4349 /* We do not support '!' for function probes */
4350 if (WARN_ON(glob[0] == '!'))
4351 return -EINVAL;
4352
4353
4354 mutex_lock(&ftrace_lock);
4355 /* Check if the probe_ops is already registered */
4356 list_for_each_entry(probe, &tr->func_probes, list) {
4357 if (probe->probe_ops == probe_ops)
4358 break;
4359 }
4360 if (&probe->list == &tr->func_probes) {
4361 probe = kzalloc(sizeof(*probe), GFP_KERNEL);
4362 if (!probe) {
4363 mutex_unlock(&ftrace_lock);
4364 return -ENOMEM;
4365 }
4366 probe->probe_ops = probe_ops;
4367 probe->ops.func = function_trace_probe_call;
4368 probe->tr = tr;
4369 ftrace_ops_init(&probe->ops);
4370 list_add(&probe->list, &tr->func_probes);
4371 }
4372
4373 acquire_probe_locked(probe);
4374
4375 mutex_unlock(&ftrace_lock);
4376
4377 mutex_lock(&probe->ops.func_hash->regex_lock);
4378
4379 orig_hash = &probe->ops.func_hash->filter_hash;
4380 old_hash = *orig_hash;
4381 hash = alloc_and_copy_ftrace_hash(FTRACE_HASH_DEFAULT_BITS, old_hash);
4382
4383 ret = ftrace_match_records(hash, glob, strlen(glob));
4384
4385 /* Nothing found? */
4386 if (!ret)
4387 ret = -EINVAL;
4388
4389 if (ret < 0)
4390 goto out;
4391
4392 size = 1 << hash->size_bits;
4393 for (i = 0; i < size; i++) {
4394 hlist_for_each_entry(entry, &hash->buckets[i], hlist) {
4395 if (ftrace_lookup_ip(old_hash, entry->ip))
4396 continue;
4397 /*
4398 * The caller might want to do something special
4399 * for each function we find. We call the callback
4400 * to give the caller an opportunity to do so.
4401 */
4402 if (probe_ops->init) {
4403 ret = probe_ops->init(probe_ops, tr,
4404 entry->ip, data,
4405 &probe->data);
4406 if (ret < 0) {
4407 if (probe_ops->free && count)
4408 probe_ops->free(probe_ops, tr,
4409 0, probe->data);
4410 probe->data = NULL;
4411 goto out;
4412 }
4413 }
4414 count++;
4415 }
4416 }
4417
4418 mutex_lock(&ftrace_lock);
4419
4420 if (!count) {
4421 /* Nothing was added? */
4422 ret = -EINVAL;
4423 goto out_unlock;
4424 }
4425
4426 ret = ftrace_hash_move_and_update_ops(&probe->ops, orig_hash,
4427 hash, 1);
4428 if (ret < 0)
4429 goto err_unlock;
4430
4431 /* One ref for each new function traced */
4432 probe->ref += count;
4433
4434 if (!(probe->ops.flags & FTRACE_OPS_FL_ENABLED))
4435 ret = ftrace_startup(&probe->ops, 0);
4436
4437 out_unlock:
4438 mutex_unlock(&ftrace_lock);
4439
4440 if (!ret)
4441 ret = count;
4442 out:
4443 mutex_unlock(&probe->ops.func_hash->regex_lock);
4444 free_ftrace_hash(hash);
4445
4446 release_probe(probe);
4447
4448 return ret;
4449
4450 err_unlock:
4451 if (!probe_ops->free || !count)
4452 goto out_unlock;
4453
4454 /* Failed to do the move, need to call the free functions */
4455 for (i = 0; i < size; i++) {
4456 hlist_for_each_entry(entry, &hash->buckets[i], hlist) {
4457 if (ftrace_lookup_ip(old_hash, entry->ip))
4458 continue;
4459 probe_ops->free(probe_ops, tr, entry->ip, probe->data);
4460 }
4461 }
4462 goto out_unlock;
4463}
4464
4465int
4466unregister_ftrace_function_probe_func(char *glob, struct trace_array *tr,
4467 struct ftrace_probe_ops *probe_ops)
4468{
4469 struct ftrace_ops_hash old_hash_ops;
4470 struct ftrace_func_entry *entry;
4471 struct ftrace_func_probe *probe;
4472 struct ftrace_glob func_g;
4473 struct ftrace_hash **orig_hash;
4474 struct ftrace_hash *old_hash;
4475 struct ftrace_hash *hash = NULL;
4476 struct hlist_node *tmp;
4477 struct hlist_head hhd;
4478 char str[KSYM_SYMBOL_LEN];
4479 int count = 0;
4480 int i, ret = -ENODEV;
4481 int size;
4482
4483 if (!glob || !strlen(glob) || !strcmp(glob, "*"))
4484 func_g.search = NULL;
4485 else {
4486 int not;
4487
4488 func_g.type = filter_parse_regex(glob, strlen(glob),
4489 &func_g.search, &not);
4490 func_g.len = strlen(func_g.search);
4491
4492 /* we do not support '!' for function probes */
4493 if (WARN_ON(not))
4494 return -EINVAL;
4495 }
4496
4497 mutex_lock(&ftrace_lock);
4498 /* Check if the probe_ops is already registered */
4499 list_for_each_entry(probe, &tr->func_probes, list) {
4500 if (probe->probe_ops == probe_ops)
4501 break;
4502 }
4503 if (&probe->list == &tr->func_probes)
4504 goto err_unlock_ftrace;
4505
4506 ret = -EINVAL;
4507 if (!(probe->ops.flags & FTRACE_OPS_FL_INITIALIZED))
4508 goto err_unlock_ftrace;
4509
4510 acquire_probe_locked(probe);
4511
4512 mutex_unlock(&ftrace_lock);
4513
4514 mutex_lock(&probe->ops.func_hash->regex_lock);
4515
4516 orig_hash = &probe->ops.func_hash->filter_hash;
4517 old_hash = *orig_hash;
4518
4519 if (ftrace_hash_empty(old_hash))
4520 goto out_unlock;
4521
4522 old_hash_ops.filter_hash = old_hash;
4523 /* Probes only have filters */
4524 old_hash_ops.notrace_hash = NULL;
4525
4526 ret = -ENOMEM;
4527 hash = alloc_and_copy_ftrace_hash(FTRACE_HASH_DEFAULT_BITS, old_hash);
4528 if (!hash)
4529 goto out_unlock;
4530
4531 INIT_HLIST_HEAD(&hhd);
4532
4533 size = 1 << hash->size_bits;
4534 for (i = 0; i < size; i++) {
4535 hlist_for_each_entry_safe(entry, tmp, &hash->buckets[i], hlist) {
4536
4537 if (func_g.search) {
4538 kallsyms_lookup(entry->ip, NULL, NULL,
4539 NULL, str);
4540 if (!ftrace_match(str, &func_g))
4541 continue;
4542 }
4543 count++;
4544 remove_hash_entry(hash, entry);
4545 hlist_add_head(&entry->hlist, &hhd);
4546 }
4547 }
4548
4549 /* Nothing found? */
4550 if (!count) {
4551 ret = -EINVAL;
4552 goto out_unlock;
4553 }
4554
4555 mutex_lock(&ftrace_lock);
4556
4557 WARN_ON(probe->ref < count);
4558
4559 probe->ref -= count;
4560
4561 if (ftrace_hash_empty(hash))
4562 ftrace_shutdown(&probe->ops, 0);
4563
4564 ret = ftrace_hash_move_and_update_ops(&probe->ops, orig_hash,
4565 hash, 1);
4566
4567 /* still need to update the function call sites */
4568 if (ftrace_enabled && !ftrace_hash_empty(hash))
4569 ftrace_run_modify_code(&probe->ops, FTRACE_UPDATE_CALLS,
4570 &old_hash_ops);
4571 synchronize_sched();
4572
4573 hlist_for_each_entry_safe(entry, tmp, &hhd, hlist) {
4574 hlist_del(&entry->hlist);
4575 if (probe_ops->free)
4576 probe_ops->free(probe_ops, tr, entry->ip, probe->data);
4577 kfree(entry);
4578 }
4579 mutex_unlock(&ftrace_lock);
4580
4581 out_unlock:
4582 mutex_unlock(&probe->ops.func_hash->regex_lock);
4583 free_ftrace_hash(hash);
4584
4585 release_probe(probe);
4586
4587 return ret;
4588
4589 err_unlock_ftrace:
4590 mutex_unlock(&ftrace_lock);
4591 return ret;
4592}

4594void clear_ftrace_function_probes(struct trace_array *tr)
4595{
4596 struct ftrace_func_probe *probe, *n;
4597
4598 list_for_each_entry_safe(probe, n, &tr->func_probes, list)
4599 unregister_ftrace_function_probe_func(NULL, tr, probe->probe_ops);

4605/*
4606 * Currently we only register ftrace commands from __init, so mark this
4607 * __init too.

4609__init int register_ftrace_command(struct ftrace_func_command *cmd)
4610{

4619 }

4651static int ftrace_process_regex(struct ftrace_iterator *iter,
4652 char *buff, int len, int enable)
4653{
4654 struct ftrace_hash *hash = iter->hash;
4655 struct trace_array *tr = iter->ops->private;
4656 char *func, *command, *next = buff;
4657 struct ftrace_func_command *p;
4658 int ret = -EINVAL;
4659
4660 func = strsep(&next, ":");
4661
4662 if (!next) {
4663 ret = ftrace_match_records(hash, func, len);
4664 if (!ret)
4665 ret = -EINVAL;
4666 if (ret < 0)
4667 return ret;
4668 return 0;
4669 }
4670
4671 /* command found */
4672
4673 command = strsep(&next, ":");
4674
4675 mutex_lock(&ftrace_cmd_mutex);
4676 list_for_each_entry(p, &ftrace_commands, list) {
4677 if (strcmp(p->name, command) == 0) {
4678 ret = p->func(tr, hash, func, command, next, enable);
4679 goto out_unlock;
4680 }
4681 }
4682 out_unlock:
4683 mutex_unlock(&ftrace_cmd_mutex);
4684
4685 return ret;
4686}

4688static ssize_t
4689ftrace_regex_write(struct file *file, const char __user *ubuf,
4690 size_t cnt, loff_t *ppos, int enable)
4691{
4692 struct ftrace_iterator *iter;
4693 struct trace_parser *parser;
4694 ssize_t ret, read;
4695
4696 if (!cnt)
4697 return 0;
4698
4699 if (file->f_mode & FMODE_READ) {
4700 struct seq_file *m = file->private_data;
4701 iter = m->private;
4702 } else
4703 iter = file->private_data;
4704
4705 if (unlikely(ftrace_disabled))
4706 return -ENODEV;
4707
4708 /* iter->hash is a local copy, so we don't need regex_lock */
4709
4710 parser = &iter->parser;
4711 read = trace_get_user(parser, ubuf, cnt, ppos);
4712
4713 if (read >= 0 && trace_parser_loaded(parser) &&
4714 !trace_parser_cont(parser)) {
4715 ret = ftrace_process_regex(iter, parser->buffer,
4716 parser->idx, enable);
4717 trace_parser_clear(parser);
4718 if (ret < 0)
4719 goto out;
4720 }
4721
4722 ret = read;
4723 out:
4724 return ret;
4725}

4727ssize_t
4728ftrace_filter_write(struct file *file, const char __user *ubuf,
4729 size_t cnt, loff_t *ppos)
4730{
4731 return ftrace_regex_write(file, ubuf, cnt, ppos, 1);
4732}
4733
4734ssize_t
4735ftrace_notrace_write(struct file *file, const char __user *ubuf,
4736 size_t cnt, loff_t *ppos)
4737{
4738 return ftrace_regex_write(file, ubuf, cnt, ppos, 0);
4739}

4741static int
4742ftrace_match_addr(struct ftrace_hash *hash, unsigned long ip, int remove)
4743{
4744 struct ftrace_func_entry *entry;
4745
4746 if (!ftrace_location(ip))
4747 return -EINVAL;
4748
4749 if (remove) {
4750 entry = ftrace_lookup_ip(hash, ip);
4751 if (!entry)
4752 return -ENOENT;
4753 free_hash_entry(hash, entry);
4754 return 0;
4755 }
4756
4757 return add_hash_entry(hash, ip);
4758}

4760static int
4761ftrace_set_hash(struct ftrace_ops *ops, unsigned char *buf, int len,
4762 unsigned long ip, int remove, int reset, int enable)
4763{
4764 struct ftrace_hash **orig_hash;
4765 struct ftrace_hash *hash;
4766 int ret;
4767
4768 if (unlikely(ftrace_disabled))
4769 return -ENODEV;
4770
4771 mutex_lock(&ops->func_hash->regex_lock);
4772
4773 if (enable)
4774 orig_hash = &ops->func_hash->filter_hash;
4775 else
4776 orig_hash = &ops->func_hash->notrace_hash;
4777
4778 if (reset)
4779 hash = alloc_ftrace_hash(FTRACE_HASH_DEFAULT_BITS);
4780 else
4781 hash = alloc_and_copy_ftrace_hash(FTRACE_HASH_DEFAULT_BITS, *orig_hash);
4782
4783 if (!hash) {
4784 ret = -ENOMEM;
4785 goto out_regex_unlock;
4786 }
4787
4788 if (buf && !ftrace_match_records(hash, buf, len)) {
4789 ret = -EINVAL;
4790 goto out_regex_unlock;
4791 }
4792 if (ip) {
4793 ret = ftrace_match_addr(hash, ip, remove);
4794 if (ret < 0)
4795 goto out_regex_unlock;
4796 }
4797
4798 mutex_lock(&ftrace_lock);
4799 ret = ftrace_hash_move_and_update_ops(ops, orig_hash, hash, enable);
4800 mutex_unlock(&ftrace_lock);
4801
4802 out_regex_unlock:
4803 mutex_unlock(&ops->func_hash->regex_lock);
4804
4805 free_ftrace_hash(hash);
4806 return ret;
4807}

4814}

5032int ftrace_regex_release(struct inode *inode, struct file *file)
5033{
5034 struct seq_file *m = (struct seq_file *)file->private_data;
5035 struct ftrace_iterator *iter;
5036 struct ftrace_hash **orig_hash;
5037 struct trace_parser *parser;
5038 int filter_hash;
5039 int ret;
5040
5041 if (file->f_mode & FMODE_READ) {
5042 iter = m->private;
5043 seq_release(inode, file);
5044 } else
5045 iter = file->private_data;
5046
5047 parser = &iter->parser;
5048 if (trace_parser_loaded(parser)) {
5049 parser->buffer[parser->idx] = 0;
5050 ftrace_match_records(iter->hash, parser->buffer, parser->idx);
5051 }
5052
5053 trace_parser_put(parser);
5054
5055 mutex_lock(&iter->ops->func_hash->regex_lock);
5056
5057 if (file->f_mode & FMODE_WRITE) {
5058 filter_hash = !!(iter->flags & FTRACE_ITER_FILTER);
5059
5060 if (filter_hash) {
5061 orig_hash = &iter->ops->func_hash->filter_hash;
5062 if (iter->tr && !list_empty(&iter->tr->mod_trace))
5063 iter->hash->flags |= FTRACE_HASH_FL_MOD;
5064 } else
5065 orig_hash = &iter->ops->func_hash->notrace_hash;
5066
5067 mutex_lock(&ftrace_lock);
5068 ret = ftrace_hash_move_and_update_ops(iter->ops, orig_hash,
5069 iter->hash, filter_hash);
5070 mutex_unlock(&ftrace_lock);
5071 } else {
5072 /* For read only, the hash is the ops hash */
5073 iter->hash = NULL;
5074 }
5075
5076 mutex_unlock(&iter->ops->func_hash->regex_lock);
5077 free_ftrace_hash(iter->hash);
5078 kfree(iter);
5079
5080 return 0;
5081}

5117struct ftrace_hash *ftrace_graph_hash = EMPTY_HASH;
5118struct ftrace_hash *ftrace_graph_notrace_hash = EMPTY_HASH;
5119
5120enum graph_filter_type {
5121 GRAPH_FILTER_NOTRACE = 0,
5122 GRAPH_FILTER_FUNCTION,
5123};
5124
5125#define FTRACE_GRAPH_EMPTY ((void *)1)
5126
5127struct ftrace_graph_data {
5128 struct ftrace_hash *hash;
5129 struct ftrace_func_entry *entry;
5130 int idx; /* for hash table iteration */
5131 enum graph_filter_type type;
5132 struct ftrace_hash *new_hash;
5133 const struct seq_operations *seq_ops;
5134 struct trace_parser parser;
5135};
5136
5137static void *
5138__g_next(struct seq_file *m, loff_t *pos)
5139{
5140 struct ftrace_graph_data *fgd = m->private;
5141 struct ftrace_func_entry *entry = fgd->entry;
5142 struct hlist_head *head;
5143 int i, idx = fgd->idx;
5144
5145 if (*pos >= fgd->hash->count)
5146 return NULL;
5147
5148 if (entry) {
5149 hlist_for_each_entry_continue(entry, hlist) {
5150 fgd->entry = entry;
5151 return entry;
5152 }
5153
5154 idx++;
5155 }
5156
5157 for (i = idx; i < 1 << fgd->hash->size_bits; i++) {
5158 head = &fgd->hash->buckets[i];
5159 hlist_for_each_entry(entry, head, hlist) {
5160 fgd->entry = entry;
5161 fgd->idx = i;
5162 return entry;
5163 }
5164 }
5165 return NULL;
5166}
5167
5168static void *
5169g_next(struct seq_file *m, void *v, loff_t *pos)
5170{
5171 (*pos)++;
5172 return __g_next(m, pos);
5173}
5174
5175static void *g_start(struct seq_file *m, loff_t *pos)
5176{
5177 struct ftrace_graph_data *fgd = m->private;
5178
5179 mutex_lock(&graph_lock);
5180
5181 if (fgd->type == GRAPH_FILTER_FUNCTION)
5182 fgd->hash = rcu_dereference_protected(ftrace_graph_hash,
5183 lockdep_is_held(&graph_lock));
5184 else
5185 fgd->hash = rcu_dereference_protected(ftrace_graph_notrace_hash,
5186 lockdep_is_held(&graph_lock));
5187
5188 /* Nothing, tell g_show to print all functions are enabled */
5189 if (ftrace_hash_empty(fgd->hash) && !*pos)
5190 return FTRACE_GRAPH_EMPTY;
5191
5192 fgd->idx = 0;
5193 fgd->entry = NULL;
5194 return __g_next(m, pos);
5195}
5196
5197static void g_stop(struct seq_file *m, void *p)
5198{
5199 mutex_unlock(&graph_lock);
5200}
5201
5202static int g_show(struct seq_file *m, void *v)
5203{
5204 struct ftrace_func_entry *entry = v;
5205
5206 if (!entry)
5207 return 0;
5208
5209 if (entry == FTRACE_GRAPH_EMPTY) {
5210 struct ftrace_graph_data *fgd = m->private;
5211
5212 if (fgd->type == GRAPH_FILTER_FUNCTION)
5213 seq_puts(m, "#### all functions enabled ####\n");
5214 else
5215 seq_puts(m, "#### no functions disabled ####\n");
5216 return 0;
5217 }
5218
5219 seq_printf(m, "%ps\n", (void *)entry->ip);
5220
5221 return 0;
5222}

5226 .next = g_next,
5227 .stop = g_stop,
5228 .show = g_show,
5229};
5230
5231static int
5232__ftrace_graph_open(struct inode *inode, struct file *file,
5233 struct ftrace_graph_data *fgd)
5234{
5235 int ret = 0;
5236 struct ftrace_hash *new_hash = NULL;
5237
5238 if (file->f_mode & FMODE_WRITE) {
5239 const int size_bits = FTRACE_HASH_DEFAULT_BITS;
5240
5241 if (trace_parser_get_init(&fgd->parser, FTRACE_BUFF_MAX))
5242 return -ENOMEM;
5243
5244 if (file->f_flags & O_TRUNC)
5245 new_hash = alloc_ftrace_hash(size_bits);
5246 else
5247 new_hash = alloc_and_copy_ftrace_hash(size_bits,
5248 fgd->hash);
5249 if (!new_hash) {
5250 ret = -ENOMEM;
5251 goto out;
5252 }
5253 }
5254
5255 if (file->f_mode & FMODE_READ) {
5256 ret = seq_open(file, &ftrace_graph_seq_ops);
5257 if (!ret) {
5258 struct seq_file *m = file->private_data;
5259 m->private = fgd;
5260 } else {
5261 /* Failed */
5262 free_ftrace_hash(new_hash);
5263 new_hash = NULL;
5264 }
5265 } else
5266 file->private_data = fgd;
5267
5268out:
5269 if (ret < 0 && file->f_mode & FMODE_WRITE)
5270 trace_parser_put(&fgd->parser);
5271
5272 fgd->new_hash = new_hash;
5273
5274 /*
5275 * All uses of fgd->hash must be taken with the graph_lock
5276 * held. The graph_lock is going to be released, so force
5277 * fgd->hash to be reinitialized when it is taken again.
5278 */
5279 fgd->hash = NULL;
5280
5281 return ret;
5282}

5284static int
5285ftrace_graph_open(struct inode *inode, struct file *file)
5286{
5287 struct ftrace_graph_data *fgd;
5288 int ret;
5289
5290 if (unlikely(ftrace_disabled))
5291 return -ENODEV;
5292
5293 fgd = kmalloc(sizeof(*fgd), GFP_KERNEL);
5294 if (fgd == NULL)
5295 return -ENOMEM;
5296
5297 mutex_lock(&graph_lock);
5298
5299 fgd->hash = rcu_dereference_protected(ftrace_graph_hash,
5300 lockdep_is_held(&graph_lock));
5301 fgd->type = GRAPH_FILTER_FUNCTION;
5302 fgd->seq_ops = &ftrace_graph_seq_ops;
5303
5304 ret = __ftrace_graph_open(inode, file, fgd);
5305 if (ret < 0)
5306 kfree(fgd);
5307
5308 mutex_unlock(&graph_lock);
5309 return ret;
5310}

5339
5340static int
5341ftrace_graph_release(struct inode *inode, struct file *file)
5342{
5343 struct ftrace_graph_data *fgd;
5344 struct ftrace_hash *old_hash, *new_hash;
5345 struct trace_parser *parser;
5346 int ret = 0;
5347
5348 if (file->f_mode & FMODE_READ) {
5349 struct seq_file *m = file->private_data;
5350
5351 fgd = m->private;
5352 seq_release(inode, file);
5353 } else {
5354 fgd = file->private_data;
5355 }
5356
5357
5358 if (file->f_mode & FMODE_WRITE) {
5359
5360 parser = &fgd->parser;
5361
5362 if (trace_parser_loaded((parser))) {
5363 parser->buffer[parser->idx] = 0;
5364 ret = ftrace_graph_set_hash(fgd->new_hash,
5365 parser->buffer);
5366 }
5367
5368 trace_parser_put(parser);
5369
5370 new_hash = __ftrace_hash_move(fgd->new_hash);
5371 if (!new_hash) {
5372 ret = -ENOMEM;
5373 goto out;
5374 }
5375
5376 mutex_lock(&graph_lock);
5377
5378 if (fgd->type == GRAPH_FILTER_FUNCTION) {
5379 old_hash = rcu_dereference_protected(ftrace_graph_hash,
5380 lockdep_is_held(&graph_lock));
5381 rcu_assign_pointer(ftrace_graph_hash, new_hash);
5382 } else {
5383 old_hash = rcu_dereference_protected(ftrace_graph_notrace_hash,
5384 lockdep_is_held(&graph_lock));
5385 rcu_assign_pointer(ftrace_graph_notrace_hash, new_hash);
5386 }
5387
5388 mutex_unlock(&graph_lock);
5389
5390 /* Wait till all users are no longer using the old hash */
5391 synchronize_sched();
5392
5393 free_ftrace_hash(old_hash);
5394 }
5395
5396 out:
5397 free_ftrace_hash(fgd->new_hash);
5398 kfree(fgd);
5399
5400 return ret;
5401}
5402
5403static int
5404ftrace_graph_set_hash(struct ftrace_hash *hash, char *buffer)
5405{
5406 struct ftrace_glob func_g;
5407 struct dyn_ftrace *rec;
5408 struct ftrace_page *pg;
5409 struct ftrace_func_entry *entry;
5410 int fail = 1;
5411 int not;
5412
5413 /* decode regex */
5414 func_g.type = filter_parse_regex(buffer, strlen(buffer),
5415 &func_g.search, &not);
5416
5417 func_g.len = strlen(func_g.search);
5418
5419 mutex_lock(&ftrace_lock);
5420
5421 if (unlikely(ftrace_disabled)) {
5422 mutex_unlock(&ftrace_lock);
5423 return -ENODEV;
5424 }
5425
5426 do_for_each_ftrace_rec(pg, rec) {
5427
5428 if (rec->flags & FTRACE_FL_DISABLED)
5429 continue;
5430
5431 if (ftrace_match_record(rec, &func_g, NULL, 0)) {
5432 entry = ftrace_lookup_ip(hash, rec->ip);
5433
5434 if (!not) {
5435 fail = 0;
5436
5437 if (entry)
5438 continue;
5439 if (add_hash_entry(hash, rec->ip) < 0)
5440 goto out;
5441 } else {
5442 if (entry) {
5443 free_hash_entry(hash, entry);
5444 fail = 0;
5445 }
5446 }
5447 }
5448 } while_for_each_ftrace_rec();
5449out:
5450 mutex_unlock(&ftrace_lock);
5451
5452 if (fail)
5453 return -EINVAL;
5454
5455 return 0;
5456}

5458static ssize_t
5459ftrace_graph_write(struct file *file, const char __user *ubuf,
5460 size_t cnt, loff_t *ppos)
5461{
5462 ssize_t read, ret = 0;
5463 struct ftrace_graph_data *fgd = file->private_data;
5464 struct trace_parser *parser;
5465
5466 if (!cnt)
5467 return 0;
5468
5469 /* Read mode uses seq functions */
5470 if (file->f_mode & FMODE_READ) {
5471 struct seq_file *m = file->private_data;
5472 fgd = m->private;
5473 }
5474
5475 parser = &fgd->parser;
5476
5477 read = trace_get_user(parser, ubuf, cnt, ppos);
5478
5479 if (read >= 0 && trace_parser_loaded(parser) &&
5480 !trace_parser_cont(parser)) {
5481
5482 ret = ftrace_graph_set_hash(fgd->new_hash,
5483 parser->buffer);
5484 trace_parser_clear(parser);
5485 }
5486
5487 if (!ret)
5488 ret = read;
5489
5490 return ret;
5491}

5563static int ftrace_cmp_ips(const void *a, const void *b)
5564{
5565 const unsigned long *ipa = a;
5566 const unsigned long *ipb = b;
5567
5568 if (*ipa > *ipb)
5569 return 1;
5570 if (*ipa < *ipb)
5571 return -1;
5572 return 0;
5573}
5574
5575static int ftrace_process_locs(struct module *mod,
5576 unsigned long *start,
5577 unsigned long *end)
5578{
5579 struct ftrace_page *start_pg;
5580 struct ftrace_page *pg;
5581 struct dyn_ftrace *rec;
5582 unsigned long count;
5583 unsigned long *p;
5584 unsigned long addr;
5585 unsigned long flags = 0; /* Shut up gcc */
5586 int ret = -ENOMEM;
5587
5588 count = end - start;
5589
5590 if (!count)
5591 return 0;
5592
5593 sort(start, count, sizeof(*start),
5594 ftrace_cmp_ips, NULL);
5595
5596 start_pg = ftrace_allocate_pages(count);
5597 if (!start_pg)
5598 return -ENOMEM;
5599
5600 mutex_lock(&ftrace_lock);
5601
5602 /*
5603 * Core and each module needs their own pages, as
5604 * modules will free them when they are removed.
5605 * Force a new page to be allocated for modules.
5606 */
5607 if (!mod) {
5608 WARN_ON(ftrace_pages || ftrace_pages_start);
5609 /* First initialization */
5610 ftrace_pages = ftrace_pages_start = start_pg;
5611 } else {
5612 if (!ftrace_pages)
5613 goto out;
5614
5615 if (WARN_ON(ftrace_pages->next)) {
5616 /* Hmm, we have free pages? */
5617 while (ftrace_pages->next)
5618 ftrace_pages = ftrace_pages->next;
5619 }
5620
5621 ftrace_pages->next = start_pg;
5622 }
5623
5624 p = start;
5625 pg = start_pg;
5626 while (p < end) {
5627 addr = ftrace_call_adjust(*p++);
5628 /*
5629 * Some architecture linkers will pad between
5630 * the different mcount_loc sections of different
5631 * object files to satisfy alignments.
5632 * Skip any NULL pointers.
5633 */
5634 if (!addr)
5635 continue;
5636
5637 if (pg->index == pg->size) {
5638 /* We should have allocated enough */
5639 if (WARN_ON(!pg->next))
5640 break;
5641 pg = pg->next;
5642 }
5643
5644 rec = &pg->records[pg->index++];
5645 rec->ip = addr;
5646 }
5647
5648 /* We should have used all pages */
5649 WARN_ON(pg->next);
5650
5651 /* Assign the last page to ftrace_pages */
5652 ftrace_pages = pg;
5653
5654 /*
5655 * We only need to disable interrupts on start up
5656 * because we are modifying code that an interrupt
5657 * may execute, and the modification is not atomic.
5658 * But for modules, nothing runs the code we modify
5659 * until we are finished with it, and there's no
5660 * reason to cause large interrupt latencies while we do it.
5661 */
5662 if (!mod)
5663 local_irq_save(flags);
5664 ftrace_update_code(mod, start_pg);
5665 if (!mod)
5666 local_irq_restore(flags);
5667 ret = 0;
5668 out:
5669 mutex_unlock(&ftrace_lock);
5670
5671 return ret;
5672}

5674#ifdef CONFIG_MODULES
5675
5676#define next_to_ftrace_page(p) container_of(p, struct ftrace_page, next)
5677
5678static int referenced_filters(struct dyn_ftrace *rec)
5679{
5680 struct ftrace_ops *ops;
5681 int cnt = 0;
5682
5683 for (ops = ftrace_ops_list; ops != &ftrace_list_end; ops = ops->next) {
5684 if (ops_references_rec(ops, rec))
5685 cnt++;
5686 }
5687
5688 return cnt;
5689}

5691static void
5692clear_mod_from_hash(struct ftrace_page *pg, struct ftrace_hash *hash)
5693{
5694 struct ftrace_func_entry *entry;
5695 struct dyn_ftrace *rec;
5696 int i;
5697
5698 if (ftrace_hash_empty(hash))
5699 return;
5700
5701 for (i = 0; i < pg->index; i++) {
5702 rec = &pg->records[i];
5703 entry = __ftrace_lookup_ip(hash, rec->ip);
5704 /*
5705 * Do not allow this rec to match again.
5706 * Yeah, it may waste some memory, but will be removed
5707 * if/when the hash is modified again.
5708 */
5709 if (entry)
5710 entry->ip = 0;
5711 }
5712}
5713
5714/* Clear any records from hashs */
5715static void clear_mod_from_hashes(struct ftrace_page *pg)
5716{
5717 struct trace_array *tr;
5718
5719 mutex_lock(&trace_types_lock);
5720 list_for_each_entry(tr, &ftrace_trace_arrays, list) {
5721 if (!tr->ops || !tr->ops->func_hash)
5722 continue;
5723 mutex_lock(&tr->ops->func_hash->regex_lock);
5724 clear_mod_from_hash(pg, tr->ops->func_hash->filter_hash);
5725 clear_mod_from_hash(pg, tr->ops->func_hash->notrace_hash);
5726 mutex_unlock(&tr->ops->func_hash->regex_lock);
5727 }
5728 mutex_unlock(&trace_types_lock);
5729}
5730
5731void ftrace_release_mod(struct module *mod)
5732{
5733 struct dyn_ftrace *rec;
5734 struct ftrace_page **last_pg;
5735 struct ftrace_page *tmp_page = NULL;
5736 struct ftrace_page *pg;
5737 int order;
5738
5739 mutex_lock(&ftrace_lock);
5740
5741 if (ftrace_disabled)
5742 goto out_unlock;
5743
5744 /*
5745 * Each module has its own ftrace_pages, remove
5746 * them from the list.
5747 */
5748 last_pg = &ftrace_pages_start;
5749 for (pg = ftrace_pages_start; pg; pg = *last_pg) {
5750 rec = &pg->records[0];
5751 if (within_module_core(rec->ip, mod)) {
5752 /*
5753 * As core pages are first, the first
5754 * page should never be a module page.
5755 */
5756 if (WARN_ON(pg == ftrace_pages_start))
5757 goto out_unlock;
5758
5759 /* Check if we are deleting the last page */
5760 if (pg == ftrace_pages)
5761 ftrace_pages = next_to_ftrace_page(last_pg);
5762
5763 ftrace_update_tot_cnt -= pg->index;
5764 *last_pg = pg->next;
5765
5766 pg->next = tmp_page;
5767 tmp_page = pg;
5768 } else
5769 last_pg = &pg->next;
5770 }
5771 out_unlock:
5772 mutex_unlock(&ftrace_lock);
5773
5774 for (pg = tmp_page; pg; pg = tmp_page) {
5775
5776 /* Needs to be called outside of ftrace_lock */
5777 clear_mod_from_hashes(pg);
5778
5779 order = get_count_order(pg->size / ENTRIES_PER_PAGE);
5780 free_pages((unsigned long)pg->records, order);
5781 tmp_page = pg->next;
5782 kfree(pg);
5783 }
5784}
5785
5786void ftrace_module_enable(struct module *mod)
5787{
5788 struct dyn_ftrace *rec;
5789 struct ftrace_page *pg;
5790
5791 mutex_lock(&ftrace_lock);
5792
5793 if (ftrace_disabled)
5794 goto out_unlock;
5795
5796 /*
5797 * If the tracing is enabled, go ahead and enable the record.
5798 *
5799 * The reason not to enable the record immediatelly is the
5800 * inherent check of ftrace_make_nop/ftrace_make_call for
5801 * correct previous instructions. Making first the NOP
5802 * conversion puts the module to the correct state, thus
5803 * passing the ftrace_make_call check.
5804 *
5805 * We also delay this to after the module code already set the
5806 * text to read-only, as we now need to set it back to read-write
5807 * so that we can modify the text.
5808 */
5809 if (ftrace_start_up)
5810 ftrace_arch_code_modify_prepare();
5811
5812 do_for_each_ftrace_rec(pg, rec) {
5813 int cnt;
5814 /*
5815 * do_for_each_ftrace_rec() is a double loop.
5816 * module text shares the pg. If a record is
5817 * not part of this module, then skip this pg,
5818 * which the "break" will do.
5819 */
5820 if (!within_module_core(rec->ip, mod))
5821 break;
5822
5823 cnt = 0;
5824
5825 /*
5826 * When adding a module, we need to check if tracers are
5827 * currently enabled and if they are, and can trace this record,
5828 * we need to enable the module functions as well as update the
5829 * reference counts for those function records.
5830 */
5831 if (ftrace_start_up)
5832 cnt += referenced_filters(rec);
5833
5834 /* This clears FTRACE_FL_DISABLED */
5835 rec->flags = cnt;
5836
5837 if (ftrace_start_up && cnt) {
5838 int failed = __ftrace_replace_code(rec, 1);
5839 if (failed) {
5840 ftrace_bug(failed, rec);
5841 goto out_loop;
5842 }
5843 }
5844
5845 } while_for_each_ftrace_rec();
5846
5847 out_loop:
5848 if (ftrace_start_up)
5849 ftrace_arch_code_modify_post_process();
5850
5851 out_unlock:
5852 mutex_unlock(&ftrace_lock);
5853
5854 process_cached_mods(mod->name);
5855}
5856
5857void ftrace_module_init(struct module *mod)
5858{
5859 if (ftrace_disabled || !mod->num_ftrace_callsites)
5860 return;
5861
5862 ftrace_process_locs(mod, mod->ftrace_callsites,
5863 mod->ftrace_callsites + mod->num_ftrace_callsites);
5864}
5865#endif /* CONFIG_MODULES */
5866
5867void __init ftrace_free_init_mem(void)
5868{
5869 unsigned long start = (unsigned long)(&__init_begin);
5870 unsigned long end = (unsigned long)(&__init_end);
5871 struct ftrace_page **last_pg = &ftrace_pages_start;
5872 struct ftrace_page *pg;
5873 struct dyn_ftrace *rec;
5874 struct dyn_ftrace key;
5875 int order;
5876
5877 key.ip = start;
5878 key.flags = end; /* overload flags, as it is unsigned long */
5879
5880 mutex_lock(&ftrace_lock);
5881
5882 for (pg = ftrace_pages_start; pg; last_pg = &pg->next, pg = *last_pg) {
5883 if (end < pg->records[0].ip ||
5884 start >= (pg->records[pg->index - 1].ip + MCOUNT_INSN_SIZE))
5885 continue;
5886 again:
5887 rec = bsearch(&key, pg->records, pg->index,
5888 sizeof(struct dyn_ftrace),
5889 ftrace_cmp_recs);
5890 if (!rec)
5891 continue;
5892 pg->index--;
5893 ftrace_update_tot_cnt--;
5894 if (!pg->index) {
5895 *last_pg = pg->next;
5896 order = get_count_order(pg->size / ENTRIES_PER_PAGE);
5897 free_pages((unsigned long)pg->records, order);
5898 kfree(pg);
5899 pg = container_of(last_pg, struct ftrace_page, next);
5900 if (!(*last_pg))
5901 ftrace_pages = pg;
5902 continue;
5903 }
5904 memmove(rec, rec + 1,
5905 (pg->index - (rec - pg->records)) * sizeof(*rec));
5906 /* More than one function may be in this block */
5907 goto again;
5908 }
5909 mutex_unlock(&ftrace_lock);
5910}
5911
5912void __init ftrace_init(void)
5913{
5914 extern unsigned long __start_mcount_loc[];
5915 extern unsigned long __stop_mcount_loc[];
5916 unsigned long count, flags;
5917 int ret;
5918
5919 local_irq_save(flags);
5920 ret = ftrace_dyn_arch_init();
5921 local_irq_restore(flags);
5922 if (ret)
5923 goto failed;
5924
5925 count = __stop_mcount_loc - __start_mcount_loc;
5926 if (!count) {
5927 pr_info("ftrace: No functions to be traced?\n");
5928 goto failed;
5929 }
5930
5931 pr_info("ftrace: allocating %ld entries in %ld pages\n",
5932 count, count / ENTRIES_PER_PAGE + 1);
5933
5934 last_ftrace_enabled = ftrace_enabled = 1;
5935
5936 ret = ftrace_process_locs(NULL,
5937 __start_mcount_loc,
5938 __stop_mcount_loc);
5939
5940 set_ftrace_early_filters();
5941
5942 return;
5943 failed:
5944 ftrace_disabled = 1;
5945}

6037static inline void
6038__ftrace_ops_list_func(unsigned long ip, unsigned long parent_ip,
6039 struct ftrace_ops *ignored, struct pt_regs *regs)
6040{
6041 struct ftrace_ops *op;
6042 int bit;
6043
6044 bit = trace_test_and_set_recursion(TRACE_LIST_START, TRACE_LIST_MAX);
6045 if (bit < 0)
6046 return;
6047
6048 /*
6049 * Some of the ops may be dynamically allocated,
6050 * they must be freed after a synchronize_sched().
6051 */
6052 preempt_disable_notrace();
6053
6054 do_for_each_ftrace_op(op, ftrace_ops_list) {
6055 /*
6056 * Check the following for each ops before calling their func:
6057 * if RCU flag is set, then rcu_is_watching() must be true
6058 * if PER_CPU is set, then ftrace_function_local_disable()
6059 * must be false
6060 * Otherwise test if the ip matches the ops filter
6061 *
6062 * If any of the above fails then the op->func() is not executed.
6063 */
6064 if ((!(op->flags & FTRACE_OPS_FL_RCU) || rcu_is_watching()) &&
6065 (!(op->flags & FTRACE_OPS_FL_PER_CPU) ||
6066 !ftrace_function_local_disabled(op)) &&
6067 ftrace_ops_test(op, ip, regs)) {
6068
6069 if (FTRACE_WARN_ON(!op->func)) {
6070 pr_warn("op=%p %pS\n", op, op);
6071 goto out;
6072 }
6073 op->func(ip, parent_ip, op, regs);
6074 }
6075 } while_for_each_ftrace_op(op);
6076out:
6077 preempt_enable_notrace();
6078 trace_clear_recursion(bit);
6079}
6080
6081/*
6082 * Some archs only support passing ip and parent_ip. Even though
6083 * the list function ignores the op parameter, we do not want any
6084 * C side effects, where a function is called without the caller
6085 * sending a third parameter.
6086 * Archs are to support both the regs and ftrace_ops at the same time.
6087 * If they support ftrace_ops, it is assumed they support regs.
6088 * If call backs want to use regs, they must either check for regs
6089 * being NULL, or CONFIG_DYNAMIC_FTRACE_WITH_REGS.
6090 * Note, CONFIG_DYNAMIC_FTRACE_WITH_REGS expects a full regs to be saved.
6091 * An architecture can pass partial regs with ftrace_ops and still
6092 * set the ARCH_SUPPORTS_FTRACE_OPS.
6093 */
6094#if ARCH_SUPPORTS_FTRACE_OPS
6095static void ftrace_ops_list_func(unsigned long ip, unsigned long parent_ip,
6096 struct ftrace_ops *op, struct pt_regs *regs)
6097{
6098 __ftrace_ops_list_func(ip, parent_ip, NULL, regs);
6099}
6100#else
6101static void ftrace_ops_no_ops(unsigned long ip, unsigned long parent_ip)
6102{
6103 __ftrace_ops_list_func(ip, parent_ip, NULL, NULL);
6104}
6105#endif
6106
6107/*
6108 * If there's only one function registered but it does not support
6109 * recursion, needs RCU protection and/or requires per cpu handling, then
6110 * this function will be called by the mcount trampoline.
6111 */
6112static void ftrace_ops_assist_func(unsigned long ip, unsigned long parent_ip,
6113 struct ftrace_ops *op, struct pt_regs *regs)
6114{
6115 int bit;
6116
6117 if ((op->flags & FTRACE_OPS_FL_RCU) && !rcu_is_watching())
6118 return;
6119
6120 bit = trace_test_and_set_recursion(TRACE_LIST_START, TRACE_LIST_MAX);
6121 if (bit < 0)
6122 return;
6123
6124 preempt_disable_notrace();
6125
6126 if (!(op->flags & FTRACE_OPS_FL_PER_CPU) ||
6127 !ftrace_function_local_disabled(op)) {
6128 op->func(ip, parent_ip, op, regs);
6129 }
6130
6131 preempt_enable_notrace();
6132 trace_clear_recursion(bit);
6133}
6134
6135/**
6136 * ftrace_ops_get_func - get the function a trampoline should call
6137 * @ops: the ops to get the function for
6138 *
6139 * Normally the mcount trampoline will call the ops->func, but there
6140 * are times that it should not. For example, if the ops does not
6141 * have its own recursion protection, then it should call the
6142 * ftrace_ops_assist_func() instead.
6143 *
6144 * Returns the function that the trampoline should call for @ops.
6145 */
6146ftrace_func_t ftrace_ops_get_func(struct ftrace_ops *ops)
6147{
6148 /*
6149 * If the function does not handle recursion, needs to be RCU safe,
6150 * or does per cpu logic, then we need to call the assist handler.
6151 */
6152 if (!(ops->flags & FTRACE_OPS_FL_RECURSION_SAFE) ||
6153 ops->flags & (FTRACE_OPS_FL_RCU | FTRACE_OPS_FL_PER_CPU))
6154 return ftrace_ops_assist_func;
6155
6156 return ops->func;
6157}

6209static void clear_ftrace_pids(struct trace_array *tr)
6210{
6211 struct trace_pid_list *pid_list;
6212 int cpu;
6213
6214 pid_list = rcu_dereference_protected(tr->function_pids,
6215 lockdep_is_held(&ftrace_lock));
6216 if (!pid_list)
6217 return;
6218
6219 unregister_trace_sched_switch(ftrace_filter_pid_sched_switch_probe, tr);
6220
6221 for_each_possible_cpu(cpu)
6222 per_cpu_ptr(tr->trace_buffer.data, cpu)->ftrace_ignore_pid = false;
6223
6224 rcu_assign_pointer(tr->function_pids, NULL);
6225
6226 /* Wait till all users are no longer using pid filtering */
6227 synchronize_sched();
6228
6229 trace_free_pid_list(pid_list);
6230}

6233{

6236 clear_ftrace_pids(tr);

6238 mutex_unlock(&ftrace_lock);
6239}

6307static int
6308ftrace_pid_open(struct inode *inode, struct file *file)
6309{
6310 struct trace_array *tr = inode->i_private;
6311 struct seq_file *m;
6312 int ret = 0;
6313
6314 if (trace_array_get(tr) < 0)
6315 return -ENODEV;
6316
6317 if ((file->f_mode & FMODE_WRITE) &&
6318 (file->f_flags & O_TRUNC))
6319 ftrace_pid_reset(tr);
6320
6321 ret = seq_open(file, &ftrace_pid_sops);
6322 if (ret < 0) {
6323 trace_array_put(tr);
6324 } else {
6325 m = file->private_data;
6326 /* copy tr over to seq ops */
6327 m->private = tr;
6328 }
6329
6330 return ret;
6331}

6333static void ignore_task_cpu(void *data)
6334{
6335 struct trace_array *tr = data;
6336 struct trace_pid_list *pid_list;
6337
6338 /*
6339 * This function is called by on_each_cpu() while the
6340 * event_mutex is held.
6341 */
6342 pid_list = rcu_dereference_protected(tr->function_pids,
6343 mutex_is_locked(&ftrace_lock));
6344
6345 this_cpu_write(tr->trace_buffer.data->ftrace_ignore_pid,
6346 trace_ignore_this_task(pid_list, current));
6347}
6348
6349static ssize_t
6350ftrace_pid_write(struct file *filp, const char __user *ubuf,
6351 size_t cnt, loff_t *ppos)
6352{
6353 struct seq_file *m = filp->private_data;
6354 struct trace_array *tr = m->private;
6355 struct trace_pid_list *filtered_pids = NULL;
6356 struct trace_pid_list *pid_list;
6357 ssize_t ret;
6358
6359 if (!cnt)
6360 return 0;
6361
6362 mutex_lock(&ftrace_lock);
6363
6364 filtered_pids = rcu_dereference_protected(tr->function_pids,
6365 lockdep_is_held(&ftrace_lock));
6366
6367 ret = trace_pid_write(filtered_pids, &pid_list, ubuf, cnt);
6368 if (ret < 0)
6369 goto out;
6370
6371 rcu_assign_pointer(tr->function_pids, pid_list);
6372
6373 if (filtered_pids) {
6374 synchronize_sched();
6375 trace_free_pid_list(filtered_pids);
6376 } else if (pid_list) {
6377 /* Register a probe to set whether to ignore the tracing of a task */
6378 register_trace_sched_switch(ftrace_filter_pid_sched_switch_probe, tr);
6379 }
6380
6381 /*
6382 * Ignoring of pids is done at task switch. But we have to
6383 * check for those tasks that are currently running.
6384 * Always do this in case a pid was appended or removed.
6385 */
6386 on_each_cpu(ignore_task_cpu, tr, 1);
6387
6388 ftrace_update_pid_func();
6389 ftrace_startup_all(0);
6390 out:
6391 mutex_unlock(&ftrace_lock);
6392
6393 if (ret > 0)
6394 *ppos += ret;
6395
6396 return ret;
6397}

6455/**
6456 * register_ftrace_function - register a function for profiling
6457 * @ops - ops structure that holds the function for profiling.
6458 *
6459 * Register a function to be called by all functions in the
6460 * kernel.
6461 *
6462 * Note: @ops->func and all the functions it calls must be labeled
6463 * with "notrace", otherwise it will go into a
6464 * recursive loop.
6465 */
6466int register_ftrace_function(struct ftrace_ops *ops)
6467{
6468 int ret = -1;
6469
6470 ftrace_ops_init(ops);
6471
6472 mutex_lock(&ftrace_lock);
6473
6474 ret = ftrace_startup(ops, 0);
6475
6476 mutex_unlock(&ftrace_lock);
6477
6478 return ret;
6479}
6480EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(register_ftrace_function);
6481
6482/**
6483 * unregister_ftrace_function - unregister a function for profiling.
6484 * @ops - ops structure that holds the function to unregister
6485 *
6486 * Unregister a function that was added to be called by ftrace profiling.
6487 */
6488int unregister_ftrace_function(struct ftrace_ops *ops)
6489{
6490 int ret;
6491
6492 mutex_lock(&ftrace_lock);
6493 ret = ftrace_shutdown(ops, 0);
6494 mutex_unlock(&ftrace_lock);
6495
6496 return ret;
6497}
6498EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(unregister_ftrace_function);

6500int
6501ftrace_enable_sysctl(struct ctl_table *table, int write,
6502 void __user *buffer, size_t *lenp,
6503 loff_t *ppos)
6504{
6505 int ret = -ENODEV;
6506
6507 mutex_lock(&ftrace_lock);
6508
6509 if (unlikely(ftrace_disabled))
6510 goto out;
6511
6512 ret = proc_dointvec(table, write, buffer, lenp, ppos);
6513
6514 if (ret || !write || (last_ftrace_enabled == !!ftrace_enabled))
6515 goto out;
6516
6517 last_ftrace_enabled = !!ftrace_enabled;
6518
6519 if (ftrace_enabled) {
6520
6521 /* we are starting ftrace again */
6522 if (rcu_dereference_protected(ftrace_ops_list,
6523 lockdep_is_held(&ftrace_lock)) != &ftrace_list_end)
6524 update_ftrace_function();
6525
6526 ftrace_startup_sysctl();
6527
6528 } else {
6529 /* stopping ftrace calls (just send to ftrace_stub) */
6530 ftrace_trace_function = ftrace_stub;
6531
6532 ftrace_shutdown_sysctl();
6533 }
6534
6535 out:
6536 mutex_unlock(&ftrace_lock);
6537 return ret;
6538}

6576/* Try to assign a return stack array on FTRACE_RETSTACK_ALLOC_SIZE tasks. */
6577static int alloc_retstack_tasklist(struct ftrace_ret_stack **ret_stack_list)
6578{
6579 int i;
6580 int ret = 0;
6581 int start = 0, end = FTRACE_RETSTACK_ALLOC_SIZE;
6582 struct task_struct *g, *t;
6583
6584 for (i = 0; i < FTRACE_RETSTACK_ALLOC_SIZE; i++) {
6585 ret_stack_list[i] = kmalloc(FTRACE_RETFUNC_DEPTH
6586 * sizeof(struct ftrace_ret_stack),
6587 GFP_KERNEL);
6588 if (!ret_stack_list[i]) {
6589 start = 0;
6590 end = i;
6591 ret = -ENOMEM;
6592 goto free;
6593 }
6594 }
6595
6596 read_lock(&tasklist_lock);
6597 do_each_thread(g, t) {
6598 if (start == end) {
6599 ret = -EAGAIN;
6600 goto unlock;
6601 }
6602
6603 if (t->ret_stack == NULL) {
6604 atomic_set(&t->tracing_graph_pause, 0);
6605 atomic_set(&t->trace_overrun, 0);
6606 t->curr_ret_stack = -1;
6607 /* Make sure the tasks see the -1 first: */
6608 smp_wmb();
6609 t->ret_stack = ret_stack_list[start++];
6610 }
6611 } while_each_thread(g, t);
6612
6613unlock:
6614 read_unlock(&tasklist_lock);
6615free:
6616 for (i = start; i < end; i++)
6617 kfree(ret_stack_list[i]);
6618 return ret;
6619}
6620
6621static void
6622ftrace_graph_probe_sched_switch(void *ignore, bool preempt,
6623 struct task_struct *prev, struct task_struct *next)
6624{
6625 unsigned long long timestamp;
6626 int index;
6627
6628 /*
6629 * Does the user want to count the time a function was asleep.
6630 * If so, do not update the time stamps.
6631 */
6632 if (fgraph_sleep_time)
6633 return;
6634
6635 timestamp = trace_clock_local();
6636
6637 prev->ftrace_timestamp = timestamp;
6638
6639 /* only process tasks that we timestamped */
6640 if (!next->ftrace_timestamp)
6641 return;
6642
6643 /*
6644 * Update all the counters in next to make up for the
6645 * time next was sleeping.
6646 */
6647 timestamp -= next->ftrace_timestamp;
6648
6649 for (index = next->curr_ret_stack; index >= 0; index--)
6650 next->ret_stack[index].calltime += timestamp;
6651}
6652
6653/* Allocate a return stack for each task */
6654static int start_graph_tracing(void)
6655{
6656 struct ftrace_ret_stack **ret_stack_list;
6657 int ret, cpu;
6658
6659 ret_stack_list = kmalloc(FTRACE_RETSTACK_ALLOC_SIZE *
6660 sizeof(struct ftrace_ret_stack *),
6661 GFP_KERNEL);
6662
6663 if (!ret_stack_list)
6664 return -ENOMEM;
6665
6666 /* The cpu_boot init_task->ret_stack will never be freed */
6667 for_each_online_cpu(cpu) {
6668 if (!idle_task(cpu)->ret_stack)
6669 ftrace_graph_init_idle_task(idle_task(cpu), cpu);
6670 }
6671
6672 do {
6673 ret = alloc_retstack_tasklist(ret_stack_list);
6674 } while (ret == -EAGAIN);
6675
6676 if (!ret) {
6677 ret = register_trace_sched_switch(ftrace_graph_probe_sched_switch, NULL);
6678 if (ret)
6679 pr_info("ftrace_graph: Couldn't activate tracepoint"
6680 " probe to kernel_sched_switch\n");
6681 }
6682
6683 kfree(ret_stack_list);
6684 return ret;
6685}

6687/*
6688 * Hibernation protection.
6689 * The state of the current task is too much unstable during
6690 * suspend/restore to disk. We want to protect against that.
6691 */
6692static int
6693ftrace_suspend_notifier_call(struct notifier_block *bl, unsigned long state,
6694 void *unused)
6695{
6696 switch (state) {
6697 case PM_HIBERNATION_PREPARE:
6698 pause_graph_tracing();
6699 break;
6700
6701 case PM_POST_HIBERNATION:
6702 unpause_graph_tracing();
6703 break;
6704 }
6705 return NOTIFY_DONE;
6706}

6708static int ftrace_graph_entry_test(struct ftrace_graph_ent *trace)
6709{
6710 if (!ftrace_ops_test(&global_ops, trace->func, NULL))
6711 return 0;
6712 return __ftrace_graph_entry(trace);
6713}
6714
6715/*
6716 * The function graph tracer should only trace the functions defined
6717 * by set_ftrace_filter and set_ftrace_notrace. If another function
6718 * tracer ops is registered, the graph tracer requires testing the
6719 * function against the global ops, and not just trace any function
6720 * that any ftrace_ops registered.
6721 */
6722static void update_function_graph_func(void)
6723{
6724 struct ftrace_ops *op;
6725 bool do_test = false;
6726
6727 /*
6728 * The graph and global ops share the same set of functions
6729 * to test. If any other ops is on the list, then
6730 * the graph tracing needs to test if its the function
6731 * it should call.
6732 */
6733 do_for_each_ftrace_op(op, ftrace_ops_list) {
6734 if (op != &global_ops && op != &graph_ops &&
6735 op != &ftrace_list_end) {
6736 do_test = true;
6737 /* in double loop, break out with goto */
6738 goto out;
6739 }
6740 } while_for_each_ftrace_op(op);
6741 out:
6742 if (do_test)
6743 ftrace_graph_entry = ftrace_graph_entry_test;
6744 else
6745 ftrace_graph_entry = __ftrace_graph_entry;
6746}
6747
6748static struct notifier_block ftrace_suspend_notifier = {
6749 .notifier_call = ftrace_suspend_notifier_call,
6750};
6751
6752int register_ftrace_graph(trace_func_graph_ret_t retfunc,
6753 trace_func_graph_ent_t entryfunc)
6754{
6755 int ret = 0;
6756
6757 mutex_lock(&ftrace_lock);
6758
6759 /* we currently allow only one tracer registered at a time */
6760 if (ftrace_graph_active) {
6761 ret = -EBUSY;
6762 goto out;
6763 }
6764
6765 register_pm_notifier(&ftrace_suspend_notifier);
6766
6767 ftrace_graph_active++;
6768 ret = start_graph_tracing();
6769 if (ret) {
6770 ftrace_graph_active--;
6771 goto out;
6772 }
6773
6774 ftrace_graph_return = retfunc;
6775
6776 /*
6777 * Update the indirect function to the entryfunc, and the
6778 * function that gets called to the entry_test first. Then
6779 * call the update fgraph entry function to determine if
6780 * the entryfunc should be called directly or not.
6781 */
6782 __ftrace_graph_entry = entryfunc;
6783 ftrace_graph_entry = ftrace_graph_entry_test;
6784 update_function_graph_func();
6785
6786 ret = ftrace_startup(&graph_ops, FTRACE_START_FUNC_RET);
6787out:
6788 mutex_unlock(&ftrace_lock);
6789 return ret;
6790}
6791
6792void unregister_ftrace_graph(void)
6793{
6794 mutex_lock(&ftrace_lock);
6795
6796 if (unlikely(!ftrace_graph_active))
6797 goto out;
6798
6799 ftrace_graph_active--;
6800 ftrace_graph_return = (trace_func_graph_ret_t)ftrace_stub;
6801 ftrace_graph_entry = ftrace_graph_entry_stub;
6802 __ftrace_graph_entry = ftrace_graph_entry_stub;
6803 ftrace_shutdown(&graph_ops, FTRACE_STOP_FUNC_RET);
6804 unregister_pm_notifier(&ftrace_suspend_notifier);
6805 unregister_trace_sched_switch(ftrace_graph_probe_sched_switch, NULL);
6806
6807 out:
6808 mutex_unlock(&ftrace_lock);
6809}

6811static DEFINE_PER_CPU(struct ftrace_ret_stack *, idle_ret_stack);
6812
6813static void
6814graph_init_task(struct task_struct *t, struct ftrace_ret_stack *ret_stack)
6815{
6816 atomic_set(&t->tracing_graph_pause, 0);
6817 atomic_set(&t->trace_overrun, 0);
6818 t->ftrace_timestamp = 0;
6819 /* make curr_ret_stack visible before we add the ret_stack */
6820 smp_wmb();
6821 t->ret_stack = ret_stack;
6822}
6823
6824/*
6825 * Allocate a return stack for the idle task. May be the first
6826 * time through, or it may be done by CPU hotplug online.
6827 */
6828void ftrace_graph_init_idle_task(struct task_struct *t, int cpu)
6829{
6830 t->curr_ret_stack = -1;
6831 /*
6832 * The idle task has no parent, it either has its own
6833 * stack or no stack at all.
6834 */
6835 if (t->ret_stack)
6836 WARN_ON(t->ret_stack != per_cpu(idle_ret_stack, cpu));
6837
6838 if (ftrace_graph_active) {
6839 struct ftrace_ret_stack *ret_stack;
6840
6841 ret_stack = per_cpu(idle_ret_stack, cpu);
6842 if (!ret_stack) {
6843 ret_stack = kmalloc(FTRACE_RETFUNC_DEPTH
6844 * sizeof(struct ftrace_ret_stack),
6845 GFP_KERNEL);
6846 if (!ret_stack)
6847 return;
6848 per_cpu(idle_ret_stack, cpu) = ret_stack;
6849 }
6850 graph_init_task(t, ret_stack);
6851 }
6852}
6853
6854/* Allocate a return stack for newly created task */
6855void ftrace_graph_init_task(struct task_struct *t)
6856{
6857 /* Make sure we do not use the parent ret_stack */
6858 t->ret_stack = NULL;
6859 t->curr_ret_stack = -1;
6860
6861 if (ftrace_graph_active) {
6862 struct ftrace_ret_stack *ret_stack;
6863
6864 ret_stack = kmalloc(FTRACE_RETFUNC_DEPTH
6865 * sizeof(struct ftrace_ret_stack),
6866 GFP_KERNEL);
6867 if (!ret_stack)
6868 return;
6869 graph_init_task(t, ret_stack);
6870 }
6871}
6872
6873void ftrace_graph_exit_task(struct task_struct *t)
6874{
6875 struct ftrace_ret_stack *ret_stack = t->ret_stack;
6876
6877 t->ret_stack = NULL;
6878 /* NULL must become visible to IRQs before we free it: */
6879 barrier();
6880
6881 kfree(ret_stack);
6882}
